OL,7,F"For those reasons, we concluded that
OL,8,Fthe ad was irresponsible and likely to
OL,9,Fcause unjustified distress and serious
OL,10,Fand widespread offence."
OL,12,FThe ASA ruled that the ad must not
OL,13,Fappear again in the form complained
OL,14,Fabout, adding: "We told Viva! to
OL,15,Fensure that future ads were prepared
OL,16,Fresponsibly and did not contain
OL,17,Fcontent that was likely to cause
OL,18,Fserious or widespread offence or
OL,19,Funjustified distress to viewers."
