OL,7,FThe founder and director of Viva!,
OL,8,FJuliet Gellatley, said: "We strongly
OL,9,Freject the ASA's decision. The charity
OL,10,Funderstand that this is a deeply
OL,11,Fsensitive topic and care had been
OL,12,Ftaken to ensure the scene was
OL,13,Fobviously symbolic; a fantasy rather
OL,14,Fthan literal.
OL,16,F"The aim was to shine a light on
OL,17,Fanimal suffering in a way that
OL,18,Fconnects emotionally, not to
OL,19,Ftrivialise human grief.
